ty International, and the UN resolution of 1975 labeling Zionism as racism. The result is a book that challenges long-held assumptions about the history of human rights and offers a startlingly new perspective on the roots of the Israeli-Palestinian conflict.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aHuman rights workersvBiography. 0aHuman rightsxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300235067423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300235067.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles